extendedInfo.description: The American Heart Association Walking Paths ApplicationNow you can create, find and track Walking Paths anytime, anywhere with the American Heart Association Walking Path App. Create paths on the go, find paths near you, start walking and get healthy!Sync the app to your American Heart Association account and easily access your saved info and favorite paths from your phone. http://www.startwalkingnow.org/start_walking_paths.jsp

reviews.title: Unusable
reviews.comment: I had a hard time believing all the negative reviews, but I\'m a believer now. Advertising partially obscures the username and password fields on the login screen, making data entry very difficult. And the login button had absolutely NO effect, the login screen just sat there doing nothing. I gave it one star because it looks nice. Bleah.
reviews.author: Roger Chaplin

reviews.title: Very disappointed
reviews.comment: This app is garbage in its current form. Can\'t login can\'t see paths.  What use is it? Next time AHA puts their goods name on something, it had better work.
reviews.author: Andrea Riska

reviews.title: Too bad
reviews.comment: Force close every time. Could be a very useful app but it\'s a joke in its current form. How disappointing.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Worst App used on Android
reviews.comment: I have to say this is the worst app I\'ve ever used on Android.  We attempted the App on two different Androids with the same disappointing results.  The app is unresponsive and drains battery life.  If it is developed and fixed properly it would have massive potential.  Unfortunately, the app was released in a non-responsive state and continues to get bad reviews.  If and when it is fixed it will be too late due to the reviews being so horrible.  It should just be removed until fixed so that it can have a better outlook for the future.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: really drains battery
reviews.comment: There\'s potential for this app; however, I cannot recommend it in its present state. After one usage, it drained the battery to next to nothing. So, it\'s not worth using for me at the moment.
reviews.author: A Google User
